RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 1 1 1/8M Turf CR: 87. Maiden Special Weight Purse 67000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Weight, 124 lbs. (Non-Starters For A Claiming Price Of $40,000 Or Less In Their Last Starts Preferred). (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CHLOE'S CROWN stalked the pace from inside, ran up behind the leader on the far turn and had to pause momentarily, tipped off the rail in the lane, drew alongside the runner-up late and drove past. SAREEHA (IRE) came out in the beginning, went up to take control while keen early racing first time through the stretch, controlled the pace to the far turn, roused with a quarter mile left to run, put to left handed urging in the furlong grounds and while still clear, then got run down by CHLOE'S CROWN in the final strides. EXIT SOUL hopped slightly at the start, was closest in pursuit outside the leader in the two path to the far turn, chased between rivals into the drive, lost momentum in the furlong grounds and churned on to hold the show. INFINITE EMPIRE got floated out by SAREEHA (IRE) at the start, steadied behind that rival then started to pull and became rank, stalked the pace outside a rival, took aim three deep into the stretch but flattened out in the final furlong. TALENTED LADY hit the gate and came away slow, lagged behind under coaxing, eased off the rail and came three wide into the stretch and failed to menace. TIZ MY PRINCESS settled on the inside, angled three wide leaving the far turn and failed to menace.

ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked inside, paused 1/4, tipped out, got up

RACE.RACE_TEXT: San Vicente S. - Grade2 SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 2 7F Dirt CR: 98. Stakes Purse 200000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS. Non-Winners of a Sweepstakes allowed 2 lbs. Non winners of A Race other than Maiden, Claiming or Starter allowed 4 lbs. A trophy will be pre sented to the winning owner.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HAVNAMELTDOWN sped to the front from inside, coaxed along on the turn, urged left handed in upper stretch, continued clear into the final sixteenth while switching to the right hand and held safely under steady handling late. FAUSTIN brushed with FORT WARREN leaving the chute, stalked the pacesetter on the inside into the turn, roused on the turn while moving to the two path, chased the winner through the lane and whittle the gap late while clearly second best. FORT WARREN brushed with FAUSTIN leaving the chute, moved out into the clear then raced a bit green with his head turned up the backstretch, angled down to the rail around the bend and was along for the show. MAN CHILD raced up close to the outside of the winner, chased outside FAUSTIN on the turn, three wide into the lane and faded.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: GOLDEN AGAIN bumped with outer rival leaving the gate, stalked out of range early on, rounded the bend two wide, challenged from outside with a furlong remaining, took over and cleared MISS BELLIMBUSTO and held safely over the runner-up. GRAZED MY HEART unhurried in the beginning, went two wide into the turn, moved to the rail then went between runners around the bend, moved out then drifted out a bit in the stretch, corrected with the right hand and finished determinedly but was too late. MISS BELLIMBUSTO vied three deep then dueled from outside up the backstretch, cleared inner rival at the five-sixteenths pole, showed the way two wide into the stretch, challenged at the eighth pole and relinquished the lead in midstretch, then flattened to third. BALENCIAGA BETTY was off a bit slow to begin, trailed up the backstretch, went two wide around the bend, moved out in the lane and summoned a mild rally. DADDY CLASSY DILL bobbled crossing over the dirt, steadied briefly behind a rival nearing the half-mile pole, took the turn three then four wide and improved position. HIALEAH HOTTIE went up to vie for the lead inside a pair of rivals then dueled with MISS BELLIMBUSTO up the backstretch, lost touch with that rival at the five-sixteenths pole and retreated. BLACKENED broke a step slow, bumped and had her path taken at the start, chased on the inside off the pace, eased off the rail around the bend, moved out in the lane and weakened. BYE BYE BUGGSY hopped a bit at the start, traveled in mid-pack two wide, came three wide into the stretch, drifted to the rail and failed to menace. SMOKEM FOR YOU vied between then ceded control and moved inside to chase, dropped back along the rail on the turn and faded.
